The paper deals with the online $k$-PCA problem, which is a machine learning problem related to dimensionality reduction. The paper discusses updates for this problem and derives a new update that is more efficient and has a probabilistic interpretation. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), statistics (cs.ST), and information theory (cs.IT).
